rComments: This prof is very friendly and caring towards her students. Her lectures are at times very slow and long, but they explain everything very well. There are lots of assignments to do, but they are all very reasonable, and you have plenty of time to do them. Overall, very good prof.

Professor Soleimani is a great professor. The lectures might be a bit long and dragged but she does help by showing many demonstrations. Class structure is pretty good because this class mostly depended on assignments and improving coding skills through the assignments rather than large tests and exams. Great way to learn coding with no experience.
